Dalmatia, to which the name of Illyricum more properly belonged, was a long, but narrow tract, between the Save and the Adriatic. The best part of the sea-coast, which still retains its ancient ap- pellation, is a province of the Venetian state, and the seat of the little republic of Ragusa. The inland parts have assumed the Sela-.- vonian names of Croatia and Bosnia ; the former obeys an Austrian governor, the latter a Turkissi patha 3 but the whole country is still infested by tribes of barbarians, whose savage independence irregu- larly marks the doubtful limit of the Christian and Mahometan power ⁸⁰.
